BT /F2 9 Tf 54 808 Td (Smart Attendance and Proxy Detection System) Tj ET
54 798 m 541 798 l S
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 790 Td (and controller execution.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 767 Td (Q9. What is the role of MongoDB?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 751 Td (A. MongoDB stores users, QR sessions, attendance records, timetable entries, and document) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 737 Td (metadata.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 714 Td (Q10. What is Mongoose used for?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 698 Td (A. Mongoose defines schemas, models, indexes, validation rules, and provides database query) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 684 Td (APIs.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 661 Td (Authentication) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 637 Td (Q11. How does login work?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 621 Td (A. The user submits role, identifier, and password. Backend validates input, finds the user,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 607 Td (compares bcrypt password hash, signs a JWT, and returns token plus user details.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 584 Td (Q12. Why is bcrypt used?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 568 Td (A. bcrypt hashes passwords with salt, so plain passwords are not stored in the database.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 545 Td (Q13. What is JWT?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 529 Td (A. JWT is a signed token that carries user identity and role. The backend verifies it before) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 515 Td (allowing protected API access.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 492 Td (Q14. How is role-based access implemented?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 476 Td (A. `authenticate` verifies the token and `authorize` checks whether the user's role is) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 462 Td (allowed for the route.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 439 Td (Q15. Why should JWT secret be stored in environment variables?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 423 Td (A. Secrets must not be hardcoded because anyone with source access could forge tokens.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 400 Td (QR Attendance) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 376 Td (Q16. How is the QR code generated?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 360 Td (A. Backend creates a QR session, signs session metadata using HMAC SHA-256, converts it into) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 346 Td (a QR image data URL, and sends it to the frontend.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 323 Td (Q17. What does the QR payload contain?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 307 Td (A. It contains type, version, session ID, teacher ID, subject, section, QR token, issued) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 293 Td (time, expiry time, and signature.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 270 Td (Q18. Why is the QR signed?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 254 Td (A. Signing prevents students from editing QR fields such as subject, expiry, session ID, or) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 240 Td (section.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 217 Td (Q19. What happens when QR expires?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 201 Td (A. The scan API rejects it because current time is greater than session expiry time.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 178 Td (Q20. How does the system prevent duplicate attendance?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 162 Td (A. It checks existing records for the same student and QR session, and for the same student,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 148 Td (subject, and date.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 125 Td (Q21. How is proxy attendance reduced?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 109 Td (A. The system checks JWT identity, QR signature, session validity, student section, GPS) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 95 Td (distance, GPS accuracy, client scan ID, and duplicate attendance.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 72 Td (Q22. What is Haversine distance?) Tj ET
54 42 m 541 42 l S
BT /F1 9 Tf 497 28 Td (Page 14) Tj ET
